[DQC.US.0198.10652] The filer has reported a value for the concept us-gaap:EffectiveIncomeTaxRateReconciliationAtFederalStatutoryIncomeTaxRate with a value of 0.25. This value should be calculated by taking the value of us-gaap:IncomeTaxReconciliationIncomeTaxExpenseBenefitAtFederalStatutoryIncomeTaxRate with a value of -41,509 divided by the value of netincome of 150,700 (rounded 4d). This equals -0.2754 (rounded 4d). Please provide the equivalent percentage amount for this concept of 0.25. The value for net income should be calculated as the value of IncomeTaxExpenseBenefit divided by the value of EffectiveIncomeTaxRateContinuingOperations. Consider changing the decimal values of the percentage from inf to a decimal value that reflects the rounding used or 2 decimal places.
